article.description: — Armon Harried scored 15 points as Binghamton beat Maine 51-50 on Saturday to end a five-game losing streak.
article.headline: Harried scores 15 points, Torrence hits late jumper to lift Binghamton over Maine 51-50
article.linkText: Harried scores 15 points, Torrence hits late jumper to lift Binghamton over Maine 51-50
article.story: BANGOR, Maine -- — Armon Harried scored 15 points as Binghamton beat Maine 51-50 on Saturday to end a five-game losing streak. Binghamton's Symir Torrence hit a jumper with four seconds left and Ja’Shonte Wright-McLeish missed a 3 at the buzzer for Maine to end it. Harried also added eight rebounds for the Bearcats (9-10, 1-5 America East Conference). Nehemiah Benson added 12 points and Tariq Balogun 11. Torrence finished with six points to go with six rebounds, five assists and two steals. Jaden Clayton led the way for the Black Bears (10-11, 2-4) with 15 points. Quion Burns added 13 points for Maine. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
